external_knowledge:
embraced the recommendations = accepted the recommendation (is_accepted = 1);
beloved gadgets = preferred device;
typical length of time = average session duration;

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM user_recommendations
WHERE is_accepted = 1;

SELECT *
FROM user_sessions
WHERE session_duration > (SELECT AVG(session_duration) FROM user_sessions);

SELECT username, user_engagement_score
FROM users
WHERE user_engagement_score > (
    SELECT AVG(user_engagement_score)
    FROM users
);

external_knowledge:
- "active users" refers to users whose 'is_active' status is set to 1;
- "haven't embraced any suggestions" implies that they have not accepted any recommendations, where 'is_accepted' is 0 or null for all their recommendations;
- "embraced" metaphorically means to accept or agree to the recommendations.
